<MainLayout
  title="About Me"
  description="Who I am, how my work has evolved across market research, UX research, product analytics, and data science, and what kind of problems I enjoy working on."
>
  <section class="content-shell about-reading-shell">
    <article class="about-story">
      <h1 class="page-title about-story-title">Who I am</h1>

      <div class="about-story-prose">
        <p class="about-story-lead">
          I’m originally from China and have been living in the Netherlands for the past few years.
          I have an academic background in both psychology and data science, and over time my work
          has taken me across market research, UX research, product analytics, and analytics more
          broadly.
        </p>

        <p>
          I spent more than seven years working in international market research, leading
          quantitative and mixed-methods projects to understand consumer behaviour and support
          business decisions. Later, I became more interested in how people behave in product
          contexts and how insights can be translated more directly into product decisions, which
          led me into UX research and product analytics. That shift eventually led me to study data
          science, as I wanted to build a stronger foundation in statistics and modern analytical
          methods. For me, these are not separate career chapters so much as one continuous path:
          understanding behaviour, asking better questions, and turning different kinds of data into
          clear, useful decisions. My recent academic work in data science went very well, and it
          gave me the confidence to work much more deeply with technical tools and analytical
          workflows.
        </p>

        <p>
          I’m someone who enjoys both the people side and the problem-solving side of work. I’m
          naturally outgoing, talkative, and easy to collaborate with, and I’ve always valued
          building good relationships with colleagues and friends. At the same time, I’m highly
          organised, strong in execution, and usually the person who notices patterns,
          inconsistencies, or practical details that others miss. I like making things clearer, more
          structured, and more workable — whether that means shaping a research question, cleaning
          up a messy analysis process, or finding a way through a problem in everyday life.
        </p>

        <p>
          Outside work, I enjoy learning new things and following whatever catches my curiosity. I
          like cooking, experimenting with coffee and tea, listening to podcasts, travelling, and
          exploring topics like consumer tech and AI tools. Lately, I’ve also been experimenting
          with AI-assisted building and “vibe coding” through small projects, including this website
          itself. I like the feeling of picking something up quickly, figuring out how it works, and
          making it useful.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
